    "date": "2020-12-30T15:31:11Z",
    "text": "Safe Drugs Act\n\nThis bill authorizes the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) to order the mandatory recall of any drug when the FDA determines that there is a reasonable probability that the drug would cause serious adverse health consequences or death.\n\nCurrently, the FDA may order a mandatory recall under such circumstances only with respect to a controlled substance."
